		(descr "Juken Swiss X40.879 dual-shaft stepper, direct PCB mount, both shafts through the board. Geometry from the factory STEP (X40 v5) cross-checked against the X27 base-spec recommended PCB layout (SP-X27-e-C Fig. 6): 4 external-coil pins 0.25x0.5 mm on a 22.86 x 7.62 grid -> 0.8 mm drills; 4 internal-coil rim tails at (+-13.96, +-6.36) -> 1.8 mm drills; 3 snap pegs D2.5 -> 3.0 mm NPTH; shaft boss D3.0 at (0,-6) -> 4.6 mm NPTH clearance. Motor body D31.5, mounts on the OPPOSITE side of the dial: place this footprint on the back in layout (flip) so the shafts exit the front. Pin numbers per SP-X40-e-A-Pinout: 1-4 = 1e-4e external shaft, 5-8 = 1i(5) 2i(6) 3i(7) 4i(8) internal shaft.")
		(tags "stepper motor Juken X40 X40.879 dual shaft gauge")
